*   Common linked list operations include `insert`, `delete`, and `traverse`.

### Hash Table
A hash table is a data structure that maps keys to values using a hash function.

$H: K \to V$

*   A hash table can be implemented using separate chaining or open addressing.
*   Common hash table operations include `insert` and `search`.

## Math Formulas
----------------

$$\text{Time Complexity}: O(1), O(log n), O(n), O(n log n)$$

In a stack, the time complexity of pushing and popping elements is constant, i.e., $O(1)$.

$$\text{Space Complexity}: O(n), O(m)$$

A linked list requires additional space to store the pointers between nodes, making its space complexity linear with respect to the number of elements, i.e., $O(n)$.

